
Makani Power is an Alameda, California-based company that develops airborne wind turbines with the support of Google and the U.S. Department of Energy office of ARPA-E.  According to some experts in the field, Makani is currently the world leader in the development of airborne wind power extraction systems.[tpl]cite news|last=Kirsner|first=Scott|title=A generator that’s lighter than air — and relatively light on the wallet|url=http://articles.boston.com/2011-04-17/business/29428335_1_wind-turbines-cape-wind-project-wind-power|publisher=Boston Globe[/tpl] 
